summary: I personally enjoyed Sansa’s coronation. I still can’t watch it without crying because seeing my girl thrive makes me so...
body: I personally enjoyed Sansa’s coronation. I still can’t watch it without crying because seeing my girl thrive makes me so emotional. Needless to say that her siblings weren’t there because otherwise the cool final montage wouldn’t have been possible. Also, the fact that they’re in different places doesn’t mean that they’re never going to see each other again. Arya will come back home someday, Bran will visit her sister (or the other way around even though Sansa doesn’t like being in King’s Landing), and Jon will pull an uncle Benjen and be home as soon as possible.

body:
Modern Brandrick + Movie Nights

  • They love having super soft nights in with lots of blankets, popcorn, hot chocolate, cuddles on the sofa, and crazy amounts of movies
  • Bran wasn’t really a movie person as a kid so Pod loves introducing him to new stuff
  • Bran has a weird knack for guessing the ending / plot twists in everything they try to watch and it infuriates Pod that nothing takes Bran by surprise
  • Pod cries at almost everything they watch, happy or sad, and Bran will just cuddle him a bit tighter, pass him a tissue and smile fondly because oh my god his boyfriend’s so cute
  • They both like pretty much every kind of movie so they can watch a wild range in a night going from Fight Club to Les Mis to Over the Hedge all in a row
  • Bran’s usually a night owl, but something about being all cosy, using Pod as a human teddy bear, with a movie playing in the background somehow leaves him unable to stay awake past about 8pm
  • Sometimes Pod will notice he’s asleep, turn the movie off and carry him up to bed
  • Sometimes it’ll be one of Pods favourites and he’ll keep prodding Bran to keep him awake so that he doesn’t miss anything
  • Their favourite movie to put on when either of thems had a bad day is Princess Diaries 2 and they aren’t ashamed to say it
  • Bran and Pod’s movie nights are the stuff of legend amongst their friends and family and only a few people have been lucky enough to ever score an invite
  • Everyone knows that you never ask Bran or Podrick to do anything on a Wednesday night because the answer will of course be a resounding no - they wouldn’t miss movie night for anything

summary: I can't believe I came into Game of Thrones for the fantasy, the dragons, the medieval theme and the magic to Season 8 ending in...
body:
I can’t believe I came into Game of Thrones for the fantasy, the dragons, the medieval theme and the magic to Season 8 ending in George Orwell’s 1984.

The big brother is watching. Or in this case the little brother. And he’s in power, there’s no place for a rebellion or to put a feet out of place.

summary: Modern AU where Bran gets paralyzed from doing dumb parkour shit. Becomes a hacker to stave off boredom and depression. Hacks...
body:
Modern AU where Bran gets paralyzed from doing dumb parkour shit. Becomes a hacker to stave off boredom and depression. Hacks local CCTV cameras to spy on people, learns a lot of shit no one wants him to know. Starts building little black drones (his “ravens”) to spy on people even better. Uncovers a dastardly conspiracy, accidentally gets found out, must temporarily run away from home with the help of his little brother, his crazy nurse, his family’s aphasiac grounds keeper, and his best friends/weed dealers (with whom he is in love).

Winds up saving the world, or at least doing something cool enough to put someone bad in jail and get him on the local news.

Hacks local CCTV cameras to spy on people, learns a lot of shit no one wants him to know. Starts building little black drones (his “ravens”) to spy on people even better. Uncovers a dastardly conspiracy, accidentally gets found out, must temporarily run away from home with the help of his little brother, his crazy nurse, his family’s aphasiac grounds keeper, and his best friends/weed dealers (with whom he is in love).

Winds up saving the world, or at least doing something cool enough to put someone bad in jail and get him on the local news.
